In a world where Mr. Mueller was the only investigator, the pressure for a comprehensive report to the public would be overwhelming.
This is where the “witch hunt” attacks on Mr. Mueller may have backfired.
For 19 months, Mr. Trump and his team have had one target to shoot at, and that target has had limited jurisdiction.
Their powers and scope go well beyond Mr. Mueller’s circumscribed mandate; they go to Mr. Trump’s judgment and whether he lied to the American people.
Mr. Jaworski is analogous to Mr. Mueller — indeed, his appointment was a model for the special counsel regulations.